      • isLeaf

        public boolean isLeaf()
        Description copied from interface: PbcsMemberProperties
        Convenience method that checks whether the given member is a leaf node (level-0) or not. Effectively this should always be true in the case that getChildren().size() == 0. This should also be true in case getChildren() returns null, although valid implementations of this interface should return an empty collection instead of null.
        Specified by:
        isLeaf in interface PbcsMemberProperties
        Returns:
        true if this member has no children and is a level-0/leaf node, false otherwise.

      • getLevel

        public int getLevel()
        Description copied from interface: PbcsMemberProperties
        Gets the calculated level of the member. The level appears to come back in the member info payload, however, it always has a value of 0. I believe this is an oversight on Oracle's part.
        Specified by:
        getLevel in interface PbcsMemberProperties
        Returns:
